summary.para: This class is available in Office 2007 and above.
When the object is serialized out as xml, it's qualified name is v:background.

remarks.format:
## Remarks [!INCLUDE[openxmlnoticeiso](~/includes/openxmlnoticeiso.md)]
`background (Document Background)`
This element describes the fill of the background of a page using vector graphics fills. Fills consist of simple colors, more advanced effects defined through the fill element (§14.1.2.5), or images.
[*Example*: The following shades the page background a pale red:
```xml <v:background fillcolor="#c0504d"> </v:background> ```
This uses the fill element (§14.1.2.5) to create a gradient background fill:
```xml <v:background> <v:fill type="gradient" color="#c0504d" color2="#f0504d" angle="45"/> </v:background> ```
*end example*]
|Parent Elements| |---------------------| |background (Part 1, §17.2.1); object (Part 1, §17.3.3.19); pict (§9.2.2.2); pict (§9.5.1)|
|Child Elements|Subclause| |--------------------|---------------| |fill (Shape Fill Properties)|§14.1.2.5|
[*Note*: The W3C XML Schema definition of this element’s content model (CT_Background) is located in §A.6.1. *end note*]
[!INCLUDE[openxmlnoticeiso](~/includes/openxmlcopyrightiso.md)]
